Booking.com Test

This past October Booking’s homepage performed an experiment where instead of showing 5 location tiles, they tested a version that only showed 3 tiles at a time with an ability to slide for more - a carousel. They measured the total sales by day.

Amazon Tests

Amazon ran an A/B test where they changed the classic list layout to a grid layout on certain product listing page. They measured the difference in purchase rates between the two layouts.

Preliminaries

First the Analysts at Amazon completed a preliminary sample size study. They were interested in finding a difference in purchase rates of 5%. Their current purchase rate is 3.45%

Parachute Effectiveness Study

The United States Air Force performed a parachute effectiveness study in the Summer of 2020. The study consisted of 20 randomly selected college students who were randomly assigned to have a parachute or not. Those who were assigned to have no parachute put on a fake parachute pack. The 30 personnel were flown to a height of 3000ft and instructed to jump out of the plane in a specified order. The ground crew measured survival of the personnel. Of course the study was double blind (meaning the personnel nor the crew who was given the fake parachute packs). Below is the code for the two levels of randomization.
